            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Also looks like the consequence of `nvim_buf_set_lines()` and `nvim_buf_set_text()` removing all marks from affected region. In this case `<` and `>`. neovim/neovim#19832 is a good reference here.\r\n\r\nOne workaround is to use `vim.cmd('lockmarks vim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(...)')`.",
